author: Houston Chronicle
title: Fast food employee killed in robbery
text:
Fast food employee killed in robbery Houston Chronicle Published 9:34 pm, Wednesday, February 22, 2017 
Police are investigating a fatal shooting at a fast-food restaurant in southeast Houston. 
According to initial reports, two people forced their way into a Subway restaurant about 9 p.m. to stage a robbery. 
During the hold-up, they shot and killed an employee, Houston police officials said. 
The shooting victim has not been identified. 
Police have not released any details about the suspects. 
Anyone with information is asked to contact Crime Stoppers at 713-222-TIPS.
